JOHANNESBURG The National Student Financial Aid Scheme (NSFAS) is calling on more than 63,000 students who receive funding to sign loan agreements before the end of the month.Those who fail to do so could forfeit their loans.The funds are paid directly to the university or training college and cover academic, residence and other student costs.READ: Extra R2bn set aside for NSFAS fundingNSFAS said payments would not be processed until a loan agreement had been signed.However, eligible students would automatically receive funding until they completed their studies, provided they pass.eNCA